article.headline: Bowling Green 52, E. Illinois 48
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Nate Miller scored 17 points and had 14 rebounds to lead Bowling Green to a 52-48 victory Saturday over Eastern Illinois. Joe Jakubowski added nine points for the Falcons (5-6), who ended a four-game skid. Bowling Green led Eastern Illinois (1-11) by 10 at halftime, which enabled them to scrape by with the win despite being outscored 35-29 in the second half. The game was never tied and had only one lead change. The game was marked by abysmal shooting from both sides, with the Falcons shooting just 29.1 percent and Eastern Illinois shooting 29.8 percent. Romain Martin led Eastern Illinois with 20 points, making six of his sixteen shots, including four 3-pointers. The Falcons out-rebounded Eastern Illinois 53-38.
